Java Application for Gmail 

current phase: 4 (Tests from phase 1 and phase 2 are turned ON)

branch for correction: master

To run the project You need:
- Make sure that your MySQL server is  running on your OS
- Run  src/test/resources/CreateEmailAppDB.sql script in order to create new User And Database
- Right click on prject -> Run Maven -> Run
- Enjoy!


System Environment
The programming language is Java version 1.8 and the GUI is JavaFX.
The Gluon Scene Builder, a visual editor, is used to create much of the GUI.

The JAG(Java Application for Gmail) is depend on an external DBMS for its message store. The DBMS will be MySQL.
Additional information on MySQL and downloads of the program can be found at http://www.mysql.com.

The JDBC driver is Connector/J.
Additional information on this library can be found at http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/.
The JAG is not dependent on any specific operating system. 

It should be able to run on any computer that supports Java. 
The help system use the Oracle Help for Java library 12.1.3.0.0. 

Information on this library can be found at http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/topics/index-083946.html
The library for accessing an email server is Jodd Email (https://jodd.org/email/). 
